---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "Five years across sales, digital marketing, and enterprise platforms. ServiceNow CSA and CIS-SPM certified. Writing honestly about the journey.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<h1 class="title mb-8">The Real Story</h1>
	<div class="prose prose-sm prose-cactus max-w-none">
		<p>
			I didn't start in tech. I started on a phone, making cold calls to strangers who hung up before I finished introducing myself. That was 2020. It was humbling in the best possible way.
		</p>

		<p>
			Five years later I've worked across sales, email marketing, SEO, industrial marketing at one of Pakistan's largest cement companies, and now ServiceNow platform implementation. Each role taught me something the previous one didn't. None of them wasted.
		</p>

		<hr class="my-8 border-dashed border-border" />

		<section class="mt-8">
			<h2 class="title text-lg text-accent mb-4">The Business Foundation</h2>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
				<img
					src="/google-marketing-certification.png"
					class="h-20 w-20 object-contain"
					alt="Google Marketing Badge"
				/>
				<p class="m-0">
					MBA in Marketing from Iqra University. Google certified across digital marketing and e-commerce. But honestly — the real education happened on construction sites in Karachi convincing contractors why a product they'd never heard of was worth their trust. No classroom prepares you for that.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-12">
			<h2 class="title text-lg text-accent mb-4">The ServiceNow Layer</h2>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
				<div class="flex gap-4 items-center">
					<img
						src="/cis-spm.png"
						class="h-20 w-20 object-contain"
						alt="ServiceNow CIS-SPM Badge"
					/>
					<img
						src="/csa.png"
						class="h-20 w-20 object-contain"
						alt="ServiceNow CSA Badge"
					/>
				</div>
				<p class="m-0">
					ServiceNow Certified System Administrator. CIS-SPM certified. Currently pursuing IRM. I came to ServiceNow not as a developer looking for a platform but as a business professional looking for a system that could make organizational chaos visible and manageable. SPM does that. So does IRM. That intersection of strategy and structure is where I work.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-12">
			<h2 class="title text-lg text-accent mb-4">What I Actually Believe</h2>
			<p class="m-0">
				Change management is 90% therapy and 10% technology. Most implementations fail not because the platform is wrong but because nobody took the time to understand why people resist change in the first place. I've spent five years learning how to have that conversation — on cold calls, in cement factories, in stakeholder meetings. That experience doesn't disappear when you open a ServiceNow instance. It's the whole point.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="mt-12">
			<h2 class="title text-lg text-accent mb-4">This Site</h2>
			<p class="m-0">
				Sheikh's Sphere is where I write honestly about the journey. Not the polished LinkedIn version. The real one — including the jobs that were messy, the lessons that came from failure, and the certifications that made sense of everything that came before them. If you're building something in the ServiceNow space or just figuring out your own path, I hope something here is useful.
			</p>
		</section>

		<hr class="my-8 border-dashed border-border" />

		<section class="mt-8">
			<h2 class="title text-lg text-accent mb-4">Work With Me</h2>
			<p class="mb-4">
				I take on consulting and project work in four areas: ServiceNow SPM implementation (demand governance, portfolio setup, executive dashboards), ServiceNow IRM (risk and compliance), marketing strategy (positioning, email, SEO), and sales enablement (outreach and pipeline process). Remote-friendly, based in Pakistan.
			</p>
			<p class="m-0">
				If you're dealing with a portfolio nobody can see, a risk register living in spreadsheets, or a pipeline that isn't converting — <a href="/services/" class="text-accent hover:underline">see what I do</a> or <a href="mailto:magic.alive11@gmail.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">email me directly</a>. I reply fast.
			</p>
		</section>

		<p class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-border italic">
			Five years of figuring out how businesses actually work. Still learning. Writing about it honestly.
		</p>
	</div>
</PageLayout>